body_html:
@hnri that error indicates that the TF_BINARY_URL bash variable is empty. The pip-install instructions are here:
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/get_started/os_setup.html#pip-installation

Specifically, you're supposed to run these two lines:

export TF_BINARY_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/tensorflow-0.11.0rc0-py3-none-any.whl

sudo pip3 install --upgrade $TF_BINARY_URL

The first line exports the TF_BINARY_URL variable, while the second line does the pip install.

Closing this out, since I believe that should fix your problem. If not just comment on this issue. Thanks!
